detailedReviews.author: Ana Barros
detailedReviews.text: Probably my favorite restaurant in the Columbia area. Staff is SUPER friendly and helpful. The actual look of the restaurant with black and white mini tiles is a classic feel with a modern vibe. But most importantly, the food is UNBELIEVABLE!!! We come here all the time to get the BEC Scallion Pancakes. They are made fresh and accompanied with the perfect amount of soy sauce. Genius, absolutely genius. We tried the dim sum today after seeing their chef making them right behind the glass wall. Best dim sum I‚Äôve had in a while. I am such a big fan, I would buy merch!

detailedReviews.author: Nathali
detailedReviews.text: I spent $16 on a rather unimpressive egg and bacon sandwich served on a bagel. I had asked for my bagel to be toasted until golden and slathered with rich, creamy butter, but it arrived untouched and unbuttered. The egg and bacon portion was so scant that it scarcely filled half of the bagel, leaving me disappointed and hungry.

I could say she was one of the best among all in New York I ever met. I came from a country which is famous for its hospitality, and I have already set a high bar in my mind in terms of service and hospitality.  She smiled a lot, was friendly and not rushing me while this was my first time ordering. She is a gem, not sugar coating!

I was handed a bagel that was practically incinerated‚Äîburnt to a crisp, blackened beyond recognition‚Äîand when I politely brought it to her attention, she didn‚Äôt apologize or offer to fix it. Instead, she rolled her eyes and condescendingly told me I should‚Äôve specified that I wanted it ‚Äújust lightly toasted,‚Äù as if it‚Äôs my fault she served charcoal disguised as breakfast. The attitude, the dismissiveness, the complete lack of customer service‚Äîit was honestly shocking. If burning food and blaming the customer is standard here, then I‚Äôll take my appetite (and my business) elsewhere.

detailedReviews.text: I have been in the neighborhood for 30 years and go to Nussbaum regularly. My experience there this morning was completely unacceptable. I looked in the window and saw no line so I went in, ordered a plain bagel with regular cream cheese (spent $5.90 including tip) and watched order after order get filled, but not mine. After 20 minutes (I paid with Apple Pay so I could see when I paid), and getting really hangry, it was clear that my order wasn't printed out or was lost. I got NO apology. Nothing. not cool.

Falsely advertising as pick-a-bagel on delivery platforms. Outsourcing delivery to an external provider, Relay, that is consistently late and delivers cold food. Customer service on the phone is brusque and unhelpful with updates on the service provided, only continues to say I‚Äôm sorry without any sincerity.

Ultimately the order was partially incorrect, and hot food was cold when delivered. Not worth the effort or high price for bagels that aren‚Äôt even fresh, to order from here again with poor execution and subpar food items.

If you‚Äôre in the food business, at least get the food right and make it good.

detailedReviews.author: Liquid Blenz
detailedReviews.text:
I don‚Äôt usually write reviews, but you‚Äôve left me no choice because I‚Äôm still thinking about this *eight months later*. That one time I decided to choose your bagel shop over Absolute Bagel‚Äîonly because their line was wrapped around the corner‚Äîwas a mistake I deeply regret. This, despite the advice of my girlfriend, who warned me after visiting your spot *once* 15 years ago, back when you had the name the other way around.

Boy, was she right. $53.25 later, I experienced not only one of the worst bagels but one of the worst breakfasts of my entire life. To put it in perspective: I grew up in poverty, and I can confidently say this ranks in the top two worst breakfasts I‚Äôve ever had‚Äîand you‚Äôre not number two.

detailedReviews.author: Xenatas
detailedReviews.text: It used to be really good when the names were the other way around. Decided to take a chance and try them out again. In the past they had always messed up my orders but they had just reopened. But today I just tried to grab a black and white cookie and a fruit danish. Instead of just completing the transaction and grabbing the two pastries that were right next to him I was given a buzzer to wait, irritating but not that big of a deal. When my order was ready I told them they got my order wrong. Without even really acknowledging me they just snatched the incorrect food from my hand. And when I reached out my hand thinking they were going to hand me my new order They just kind of threw it at me and it hit the counter. Really unnecessarily hostile environment now.

The unique fusion dishes, such as the BEC wrapped in a scallion pancake, are a standout favorite among patrons, showcasing creativity and flavor. - social media marketing can showcase this strength
The consistently fresh and tasty breakfast bagels and vegan Chinese menu options are highly praised for their quality and variety. - Boostly marketing services can amplify this
improvementOpportunities: Negative reviews and reputation issues, particularly regarding customer service and food quality inconsistencies - review management can address this concern
